The right architecture is to make ContextGraph a compiled context system, not a live federation layer.

Most expensive discovery, metadata scanning, semantic mapping, ontology enrichment, and relationship construction should happen offline or asynchronously. At agent request time, ContextGraph should query its own pre-built context stores and only access an operational source when the user actually needs fresh business data.

The key principle is:

Resolve from ContextGraph; retrieve facts from enterprise systems only when necessary.

1. Three processing paths

ContextGraph should have three distinct paths:

1. Offline context-building pipeline
   Builds and continuously refreshes the context model.
2. Real-time context compilation
   Resolves the agent’s question using precomputed context.
3. Selective data execution
   Accesses only the minimum required source when fresh data is needed.
                        OFFLINE / ASYNCHRONOUS
